data.description: Are you ready to own a piece of history?  This gorgeous 1870 brick Victorian home built by W.M. Hough (cousin of James Whitcomb Riley) is ready for its next homeowner to put their mark on it.  The wrap around porch is perfect for enjoying a cool evening with family and friends.  Upon entering, you will be captivated by the original curved staircase as well as the 12' ceilings and walnut doors on the first floor.  You will note a distinctive library and billiards room as well as a welcoming kitchen-perfect for entertaining.  Journey upstairs for 2 full baths and 5 bedrooms, and on to the 3rd floor with a ballroom!  This home sits on nearly 3/4 acre lot and offers an in-ground pool (some repairs needed) as well as a detached 3 car garage.
